column4: UPDATE 1-Britain to probe if airlines deliberately split passenger groups
column5: LONDON  Feb 3 Britain's Civil Aviation Authority (CAA) said on Saturday it was beginning a review into airlines' seating policies  including whether some operators were deliberating splitting up groups of passengers travelling together.

column5: Starbucks Corp  has too many stores and its prices are too high  Wall Street analysts are starting to agree  as they seek to explain the company's cooling U.S. growth.

column4: 7th Circuit finds Starbucks not liable for boy's finger injury
column5: A federal appeals court on Friday ruled coffee chain Starbucks Corp was not responsible for a 3-year-old boy's loss of a finger at one of its stores in Chicago  finding his parents had failed to properly supervise him.

column4: AT&T merger judge says 'no big issues' in trial preparations
column5: WASHINGTON The U.S. judge who will decide if wireless and pay TV provider AT&T Inc may purchase Time Warner Inc said on Friday that he saw "no big issues" in pre-trial preparations.

column4: U.S. seeks 'substantial' fines in Fiat Chrysler emissions case -source
column5: WASHINGTON The U.S. Justice Department is seeking "substantial" civil fines from Fiat Chrysler Automobiles NV after the government filed suit accusing the company of illegally using software that led to excess emissions in 104 000 U.S. diesel vehicles sold since 2014  a person briefed on the matter said on Friday.

column4: U.S. businessman  philanthropist Jon Huntsman Sr. dead at 80
column5: Jon Huntsman Sr.  a billionaire U.S. industrialist who invented the "clamshell" fast-food container and gave away much of his fortune for cancer research  died on Friday at age 80  the corporation he founded said.

column4: Morgan Stanley is sole bidder for Stockmann's Nevsky Center property: sources
column5: MOSCOW Morgan Stanley  has become the sole bidder for Nevsky Center property in the Russian city of St Petersburg from Finnish department store chain Stockmann  after Russian real estate investor Malltech pulled out of the tender  two sources familiar with the talks told Reuters.
